  "original_title": "\u0b85\u0bb5\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0b95\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0bb5\u0bc6\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0b85\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc8 \u0b89\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0bae\u0bc0\u0bb3\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc6\u0bb1 \u0bb5\u0bc7\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0b9a\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Immediate withdrawal of notification declaring state of emergency - Bar Association of Sri Lanka",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Sri Lankan Bar Association has pointed out that declaring a state of emergency will never be a solution to the current situation in the country, and has insisted that the declaration issued by President Ranil Wickramasinghe in response to the declaration of a state of emergency should be withdrawn immediately.",
        "The Sri Lankan Bar Association has stated the above in its statement that the announcement issued by President Ranil Wickremesinghe declaring a state of emergency in the country should be withdrawn immediately and the rights of the people should be ensured.",
        "A state of emergency has been declared by the acting president 3 days prior to the election of the president for the interim government through the parliament.",
        "As already pointed out, when the state of emergency is declared, the President is empowered to issue emergency directives, repeal or amend clauses in any law other than the clauses of the Constitution.",
        "In particular, there is an opportunity to detain a person outside the court system through emergency directives. A large number of human rights abuses have been reported in the past through emergency directives.",
        "Therefore, we are of the opinion that the emergency law guidelines should not be used to suppress the legal right of the people to express their views on it, or to disable the opportunity to express their likes and dislikes regarding a particular candidate, when it is decided to hold a referendum to elect a new president in the parliament.",
        "Freedom to engage in protests and express opinions is one of the most fundamental rights of the people.",
        "Emergency directions should therefore not be used to stifle peaceful protests and free speech and should not lead to arbitrary arrests and detentions.",
        "We believe that declaring a state of emergency will never be a solution to the current situation in the country.",
        "Therefore, we insist that the announcement issued by President Ranil Wickramasinghe declaring a state of emergency should be immediately withdrawn and the basic rights of the people should be confirmed."
      ],
